To convert the fraction $\frac{9}{2}$ to a decimal, we perform the division of 9 by 2.
\[
\begin{array}{c|cc}
\multicolumn{1}{r}{} & 2 & \\
\cline{2-3}
9 & 2 & \\
\multicolumn{1}{r}{2} & 2 & \\
\cline{2-2}
\multicolumn{1}{r}{0} & 1 & \\
\end{array}
\]
We continue the division, bringing down a zero and adding a decimal point to continue the division.
\[
\begin{array}{c|cc}
\multicolumn{1}{r}{} & 2 & & \\
\cline{2-4}
9 & 2.0 & 0 & \\
\multicolumn{1}{r}{2} & 2 & 0 & \\
\cline{2-2}
\multicolumn{1}{r}{0} & 0 & 0 & \\
\end{array}
\]
The division is now complete, and we have a quotient of 4.5.
